Definition: or תִּפְאֶרֶת; from {{h6286}}; ornament (abstractly or concretely, literally or figuratively); beauty(-iful), bravery, comely, fair, glory(-ious), honour, majesty.
from {{h8608}} contracted; a tambourine; tabret, timbrel.
from {{h8591}}; a fraud; error.
from {{h6148}}; suretyship, i.e. (concretely) a pledge; hostage.
from {{h6168}}; a knife or razor (as making bare); also a scabbard (as being bare, i.e. empty); (pen-) knife, razor, scabbard, shave, sheath.
from {{h6105}}; might (plural collective); power.
a primitive root; to cheat; by analogy, to maltreat; deceive, misuse.
or תַּעְנָךְ; of uncertain derivation; Taanak or Tanak, a place in Palestine; Taanach, Tanach.
the same as {{h8598}}; Tappuach, the name of two places in Palestine, also of an Israelite; Tappuah.
from {{h5301}}; an apple (from its fragrance), i.e. the fruit or the tree (probably includ. others of the pome order, as the quince, the orange, etc.); apple (tree). See also {{h1054}}.
probably from {{h8518}}; a quiver (as slung); quiver.
(Aramaic) or תַּלְתִּי; (Aramaic), ordinal from {{h8532}}; third; third.
probably from an unused root meaning to dissever; breach; Telach, an Israelite; Telah.
from {{h8510}} and the feminine of {{h2798}}; mound of workmanship; Tel-Charsha, a place in Babylonia; Tel-haresha, Tel-harsa.
from {{h8525}}; ridged; Talmai, the name of a Canaanite and a Syrian; Talmai.
from {{h3925}}; a pupil; scholar.
a primitive root; to pile up, i.e. elevate; eminent. Compare {{h2048}}.
from an unused root meaning to accumulate; a bank or terrace; furrow, ridge.
from {{h8510}} and {{h4417}}; mound of salt; Tel-Melach, a place in Babylonia; Tel-melah.
a denominative from {{h8438}}; to crimson, i.e. dye that color; × scarlet.

from {{h5395}}; properly, a hard breather, i.e. the name of two unclean creatures, a lizard and a bird (both perhaps from changing color through their irascibility), probably the tree-toad and the water-hen; mole, swan.
a primitive root; to loathe, i.e. (morally) detest; (make to be) abhor(-red), (be, commit more, do) abominable(-y), × utterly.

a primitive root; to vacillate, i.e. reel or stray (literally or figuratively); also causative of both; (cause to) go astray, deceive, dissemble, (cause to, make to) err, pant, seduce, (make to) stagger, (cause to) wander, be out of the way.
or תֹּעִי; from {{h8582}}; error; Tou or Toi, a Syrian king; Toi, Tou.
from {{h5749}}; attestation, i.e. a precept, usage; testimony.
from {{h5927}}; a channel (into which water is raised for irrigation); also a bandage or plaster (as placed upon a wound); conduit, cured, healing, little river, trench, watercourse.
from {{h5953}}; caprice (as a fit coming on), i.e. vexation; concretely a tyrant; babe, delusion.
from {{h5956}}; a secret; thing that is hid, secret.
or תַּעֲנֻג; and (feminine) תַּעֲנֻגָה; from {{h6026}}; luxury; delicate, delight, pleasant.
from {{h6031}}; affliction (of self), i.e. fasting; heaviness.
or תּלֻנָּה; from {{h3885}} in the sense of obstinacy; a grumbling; murmuring.
a primitive root; to suspend (especially to gibbet); hang (up).
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7950}}; snow; snow.
from {{h3847}}; a garment; clothing.
or תְּלַשַּׂר; of foreign derivation; Telassar, a region of Assyria; Telassar.
from {{h3851}}; desiccation; great drought.
from {{h3811}}; distress; travail, travel, trouble.
from {{h8510}} and {{h24}}; mound of green growth; Tel-Abib, a place in Chaldaea; Tel-abib.
a primitive root; to suspend; figuratively (through hesitation) to be uncertain; by implication (of mental dependence) to habituate; be bent, hang (in doubt).
by contraction from {{h8524}}; a mound; heap, × strength.
(Aramaic) from {{h8578}}; a second time; again.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8147}}; second; second.
or תַּנְחֻם; and (feminine) תַּנְחוּמָה; from {{h5162}}; compassion, solace; comfort, consolation.
from {{h5216}}; a fire-pot; furnace, oven.
or תַּנִּים; (Ezekiel 29:3), intensive from the same as {{h8565}}; a marine or land monster, i.e. sea-serpent or jackal; dragon, sea-monster, serpent, whale.
for {{h8575}} (feminine); Tanchumeth, an Israelite; Tanhumeth.
perhaps from the same as {{h594}} through the idea of protraction; a pinnacle, i.e. extremity; tip.
from {{h5107}}; produce; fruit, increase.
from {{h5130}}; a brandishing (in threat); by implication, tumult; specifically, the official undulation of sacrificial offerings; offering, shaking, wave (offering).
from {{h5123}}; drowsiness, i.e. sleep; slumber(-ing).
from {{h8506}}; admeasurement, i.e. consummation; pattern, sum.
apparently from an unused root meaning to encompass; a wrapper or robe; garment.
from an unused root meaning; to dissever, i.e. crush; deceitful.
from {{h3615}}; completeness; perfection.
from {{h3615}}; completion; by implication, an extremity; end, perfect(-ion).
probably for {{h7827}}; the cerulean mussel, i.e. the color (violet) obtained therefrom or stuff dyed therewith; blue.

a primitive root; to balance, i.e. measure out (by weight or dimension); figuratively to arrange, equalize, through the idea of levelling (ment, estimate, test); bear up, direct, be (un-)equal, mete, ponder, tell, weigh.
from {{h8505}}; a fixed quantity; measure, tale.
the same as {{h8506}}; Token, a place in Palestine; Tochen.
probably feminine of {{h8565}}; a female jackal; dragon.
from {{h5106}}; alienation; by implication, enmity; breach of promise, occasion.
a primitive root; to present (a mercenary inducement), i.e. bargain with (a harlot); hire.
a primitive root (identical with through the idea of attributing honor); to ascribe (praise), i.e. celebrate, commemorate; lament, rehearse.
from the same root as {{h8558}}; an erection, i.e. pillar (probably for a guide-board); high heap.

from an unused root probably meaning to elongate; a monster (as preternaturally formed), i.e. a sea-serpent (or other huge marine animal); also a jackal (or other hideous land animal); dragon, whale. Compare {{h8577}}.
or תַּמְרֻק; or תַּמְרִיק; from {{h4838}}; properly, a scouring, i.e. soap or perfumery for the bath; figuratively, a detergent; × cleanse, (thing for) purification(-fying).
from {{h4843}}; bitterness (plural as collective); × most bitter(-ly).
from the same root as {{h8558}}; a palm trunk; palm tree.
(plural or (feminine) תִּמֹּרָה; (singular and plural), from the same root as {{h8558}}; (architectural) a palm-like pilaster (i.e. umbellate); palm tree.
the same as {{h8558}}; Tamar, the name of three women and a place; Tamar.
from an unused root meaning to be erect; a palm tree; palm (tree).
from {{h4487}}; a portion assigned; Timnah, the name of two places in Palestine; Timnah, Timnath, Thimnathah.

a primitive root; to complete, in a good or a bad sense, literal, or figurative, transitive or intransitive; accomplish, cease, be clean (pass-) ed, consume, have done, (come to an, have an, make an) end, fail, come to the full, be all gone, × be all here, be (make) perfect, be spent, sum, be (shew self) upright, be wasted, whole.
a primitive root; to sustain; by implication, to obtain, keep fast; figuratively, to help, follow close; (take, up-) hold (up), maintain, retain, stay (up).
plural of {{h8537}}; perfections, i.e. (techn.) one of the epithets of the objects in the high-priest's breastplate as an emblem of complete Truth; Thummim.
from {{h4529}}; liquefaction, i.e. disappearance; melt.
or תִּמְנַת סֶרַח; from {{h8553}} and {{h2775}}; portion of (the) sun; Timnath-Cheres, a place in Palestine; Timnath-heres, Timnath-serah.
from {{h4513}}; restraint; Timna, the name of two Edomites; Timna, Timnah.
patrial from {{h8553}}; a Timnite or inhabitant of Timnah; Timnite.
from {{h6327}}; a dispersal; dispersion.

or תְּמֻנָה; from {{h4327}}; something portioned (i.e. fashioned) out, as a shape, i.e. (indefinitely) phantom, or (specifically) embodiment, or (figuratively) manifestation (of favor); image, likeness, similitude.
from {{h4171}}; barter, compensation; (ex-) change(-ing), recompense, restitution.
from {{h4191}}; execution (as a doom); death, die.
of uncertain derivation; Temach, one of the Nethinim; Tamah, Thamah.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{h8539}}; a miracle; wonder.
from {{h8539}}; consternation; astonishment.
of uncertain derivation; Tammuz, a Phoenician deity; Tammuz.

or תְּמֹל; probably for {{h865}}; sometimes with	{{h8032}}; properly, ago, i.e. a (short or long) time since; especially yesterday, or day before yesterday; before (-time),   these (three) days,   heretofore,   time past, yesterday.

from an unused root meaning to stretch; properly, continuance (as indefinite extension); but used only (attributively as adjective) constant (or adverbially, constantly); elliptically the regular (daily) sacrifice; alway(-s), continual (employment, -ly), daily, (n-)ever(-more), perpetual.

from {{h8552}}; entire (literally, figuratively or morally); also (as noun) integrity, truth; without blemish, complete, full, perfect, sincerely (-ity), sound, without spot, undefiled, upright(-ly), whole.
(Aramaic) from {{h8532}}; a tertiary rank; third.
feminine from an unused root meaning to tower; something tall, i.e. (plural collective) slenderness; armoury.
(Aramaic) multiple of {{h8532}}; ten times three; thirty.
(Aramaic) masculine תְּלָתָה; (Aramaic), or תְּלָתָא; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h7969}}; three or third; third, three.
from {{h8552}}; complete; usually (morally) pious; specifically, gentle, dear; coupled together, perfect, plain, undefiled, upright.
by reduplication, from {{h8524}} through the idea of vibration; a trailing bough (as pendulous); bushy.
from {{h8552}}; completeness; figuratively, prosperity; usually (morally) innocence; full, integrity, perfect(-ion), simplicity, upright(-ly, -ness), at a venture. See {{h8550}}.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8033}}; there; × thence, there, × where.
a primitive root; to be in consternation; be amazed, be astonished, marvel(-lously), wonder.
feminine of {{h8537}}; innocence; integrity.
